cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it proposes a novel structural pruning scheme for deep neural networks. It also involves training the network for a given dataset and optimizing it for accuracy, which are common tasks in the field of neural computing. 

The paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it involves reducing the model size and interconnection needed before training, which are important topics in machine learning. 

The cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category is also a possibility as the authors demonstrate their approach on VGG-16 for CIFAR-10, which is a common dataset used in computer vision research. 

The cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category is another possibility as the paper proposes a new approach to optimizing deep neural networks, which is a common task in AI research. 

Finally, the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper mentions the Small-World model, which is a common model used in network science and social network analysis. However, the focus of the paper is on deep neural networks rather than social or information networks.
